# BizCode Backend Development Standards

## 1. ARCHITECTURE & CODE ORGANIZATION

### Domain Module Structure (Issue #77)

Organize by domain, not HTTP method. Break apart createApp.ts (1521 lines).

**Required structure:**
- server/routes/clientes/ (handlers, validation, service, repository)
- server/routes/articulos/
- server/routes/facturas/
- server/routes/rubros/
- server/routes/proveedores/
- server/middleware/ (errorHandler, logger, validateRequest, multiTenant)
- server/lib/ (errors, logger, validators)
- server/createApp.ts (<100 lines, bootstrap only)

**Three-layer architecture:**
1. Route Handler (HTTP concerns) → Service (business logic) → Repository (database)

---

## 2. ERROR HANDLING (Issue #78)

Use AppError class hierarchy:
- ValidationError (400)
- AuthenticationError (401)
- AuthorizationError (403)
- NotFoundError (404)
- ConflictError (409)
- DatabaseError (500)

Always delegate errors to centralized errorHandler middleware via next(err).

HTTP Status Codes:
- 200: GET successful
- 201: POST created
- 204: DELETE successful
- 400: Validation error
- 401: Authentication failed
- 403: Authorization denied
- 404: Not found
- 409: Conflict/duplicate
- 500: Server error

---

## 3. LOGGING & OBSERVABILITY (Issue #78)

Use Pino for structured logging. NO console.log().

Every request gets unique X-Request-ID for tracing.

Every mutation (POST/PUT/DELETE) logs AuditEvent to database.

---

## 4. REQUEST VALIDATION (Issue #79)

Use Zod schemas, not manual ValidationResult pattern.

Define schemas in routes/<domain>/validation.ts.

Use validateRequest() middleware to parse & validate.

Single schema covers both POST and PUT with .partial().

---

## 5. MULTI-TENANT SECURITY (Issue #83)

EVERY route accessing data must validate tenantId:
- Route handler: Check cliente.tenantId === req.user.tenantId
- Service layer: Always query with { where: { id, tenantId } }
- Bulk operations: Validate every imported record's tenantId scope

---

## 6. TESTING (Issue #86)

Before every commit:
```
npm run lint
npm run type-check
npm run test
npm run test:integration
npm run check:i18n
```

Coverage targets:
- Validation: 100%
- Services: >=90%
- API: >=75%
- Critical paths E2E: 100%

---

## 7. API DOCUMENTATION (Issue #76)

OpenAPI spec is source-of-truth. Document BEFORE implementation.

Every endpoint documents request/response schemas, security, permissions.

---

## 8. DATABASE & MIGRATIONS

Every schema change needs npx prisma migrate dev --name <name>.

Add indexes on frequently queried fields (tenantId, codigo, cuit).

---

## 9. AUTHENTICATION & AUTHORIZATION

Check permissions in MIDDLEWARE before route handler using requirePermission().

Session: 2-hour expiration, rate limit: 5 failures = 15 min lockout.

---

## 10. CODE QUALITY

Commit message format: <type>(<scope>): <description>
Types: feat, fix, docs, test, refactor, chore, perf

PR checklist:
- Lint, type-check, tests pass
- OpenAPI spec updated
- Error paths return correct HTTP status
- Multi-tenant validation enforced
- Logging added
- Audit events logged (if mutation)
- i18n updated (if UI changes)
- Migrations created (if schema changes)

---

## ANTI-PATTERNS TO AVOID

❌ Mix HTTP concerns in service layer
❌ Throw database errors without wrapping
❌ Validate tenantId only in service layer
❌ Log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, CUIT, PII)
❌ Ignore errors in bulk operations
❌ Use dynamic OpenAPI generation as source-of-truth

